      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MITCHELLS RUN (7) continued his strong form when he led and stuck on to be beaten 2m at his latest appearance at Redcliffe. Had recorded two wins and two placings from the previous four outings including a victory at this circuit and distance. Has to contend with a wide draw but with even luck he is capable of another strong performance. KEAYANG MOSCATO (1) was a big improver when she finished second at her most recent outing, coming from the back line to be beaten 5.7 metres when second-up at this circuit and distance. Likely to get the favours from the inside draw. Primary contender. BELMER BETTY (2) had a tough draw last time. Runner-up at this circuit and distance prior and had won three of her previous four outings. Draws well so is worth another chance. DEE TERROR (9) must be respected after coming from this row and scoring last start by 3.5 metres at this venue.",
